laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis; trace bilateral pleural effusions; normal liver, pancreas with minimal perihilar pancreatic haziness; normal spleen and adrenal glands; normal kidneys; unremarkable gastrointestinal and reproductive organs; no lymphadenopathy; mild atherosclerotic disease; unchanged chronic posterior right eleventh rib fractures and grade ___ anterolisthesis of L5 on S1 with fusion of L5 and S1; diffuse stranding throughout the subcutaneous and intra-abdominal fat reflecting a degree of anasarca.
